          <h2>Who is Association for Project Management ?</h2>
             <h2>Who is the APM?</h2>
<p>The APM, or The Association for Project Management, is a professional or=
ganization based in the United Kingdom. It aims to advance and promote the =
profession of project management. APM is the Chartered body for the project=
 profession, offering membership, qualifications, events, publications and =
online services for professionals in project, programme and portfolio manag=
ement.</p>

<h2>APM Certification Exams</h2>
<p>The APM offers a range of certifications, from the APM Project Fundament=
als Qualification (PFQ) for beginners to the APM Chartered Project Professi=
onal (ChPP) for experienced professionals. These certification exams valida=
te your knowledge and skills in project management and can enhance your cre=
dibility and employability.</p>

<h2>Step 1: Eligibility and Application</h2>
<p>Check the specific eligibility requirements for the certification you ar=
e interested in on the APM website. Once you have determined you are eligib=
le, you can apply for the examination online. You will be required to pay t=
he examination fee during this process.</p>

<h2>Step 2: Scheduling the Exam</h2>
<p>After your application has been approved, you will receive an email from=
 APM with instructions on how to schedule your exam. Examinations can be ta=
ken at various locations, or online, depending on the certification. You ca=
n choose the date and location that is most convenient for you.</p>

<h2>Step 3: Taking the Exam</h2>
<p>On the day of the exam, ensure you arrive early at the testing center. B=
ring a valid ID for verification. If you are taking the exam online, make s=
ure you have a stable internet connection and a quiet place to take the exa=
m. Follow the instructions provided to you and complete the exam within the=
 given time limit.</p>

<h2>Location Information and Website</h2>
<p>The APM is based in the UK, but they offer online exams and have various=
 exam centers worldwide. For more information about the APM, their certific=
ations, and how to apply for an exam, visit their official website: <a href=
=3D"https://www.apm.org.uk/">www.apm.org.uk</a>.</p><p></p>
